   328	# §4. Step-1 confidence and limits
   329	
   330	- Confidence on classification: <high / medium-high / medium / medium-low>
   331	- Self-flagged concerns: <where the auditor isn't sure whether something is premise-bleed vs legitimate framing>
   332	- Cross-vendor framing-leakage caveat: <where codex may not recognize subtle in-house framings; flag for Step-2 if fires>
   333	- Slice-output sampling tally: <count of slice-output sections sampled, capped at 3-5 per §5.2.5>
   334	- Source-reading tally: <count of source files read for fact-grounding, capped at 5 per §4.2>
   335	- Out-of-scope: <items the auditor noticed but did not pursue per §5.4>
   336	
   337	# §5. Non-binding disposition signal
   338	
   339	Auditor states why Logan might choose each plausible disposition (per §8). Auditor does not pick one; Logan disposes.
   340	
   341	- **Why Logan might choose commit-as-is:** <reasoning given findings>
   342	- **Why Logan might choose commit-with-addendum:** <reasoning given findings>
   343	- **Why Logan might choose revise-before-commit:** <reasoning given findings>
   344	```
   345	
   346	### §6.2 Step-2 (same-vendor stress) FINDINGS structure (if fired)
   347	
   348	Appended to the Step-1 document if Step-2 fires:
   349	
   350	```
   351	# §6. Step-2 summary
   352	- Same-vendor confirmations: N (Step-1 findings same-vendor agrees with)
   353	- Same-vendor re-classifications: M (Step-1 findings same-vendor would re-class)
   354	- Net-new same-vendor findings: P (cross-vendor missed)
   355	- Same-vendor dismissals: Q (Step-1 findings same-vendor would dismiss)
   356	
   357	# §7. Per-instance Step-2 findings
   358	[same structure as §1, scoped to Step-2 candidates]
   359	
   360	# §8. Differential analysis
   361	- Cross-vendor-only candidates (same-vendor missed): <highest-priority Class C-eligible>
   362	- Same-vendor-only candidates (cross-vendor missed): <register-shaped catches; calibrate carefully>
   363	- Joint candidates: <robustness-signaled>
   364	
   365	# §9. Step-2 confidence and limits
   366	- M1 register-catch caveat: <where same-vendor may share v1-GSD framing-leak with Claude+Logan and cannot self-detect>
   367	- Self-flagged concerns: <...>
   368	- Out-of-scope: <...>
   369	
   370	# §10. Updated non-binding disposition signal
   371	- <revised reasoning per option given combined Step-1 + Step-2 evidence>
   372	```
   373	
   374	### §6.3 Output constraints
   375	
   376	- **Length:** Step-1 only = 200-500 lines target. Step-1 + Step-2 = 350-700 lines. Beyond these, audit is over-scoped; flag instead of expanding.
   377	- **No drafting suggestions** for revised wording (Logan + Claude handle revision post-disposition).
   378	- **No reframe proposals** (out of scope).
   379	- **Calibrated language**; cite verbatim; no paraphrase substitution for direct quotes.
   380	- **Citation discipline:** every verbatim quote pairs with file:line; every grounding-cited claim pairs with prior-audit-citation or source-read-citation.
   381	
   382	## §7. Classification rubric
   383	
   384	**Class A — cosmetic / wording-addendum.**
   385	- Vocabulary appears but doesn't shape the surrounding analysis.
   386	- Could be revised by adding a footnote or 1-3 line clarification without changing downstream conclusions.
   387	- Example shape: "patcher / skills / hybrid" appears in INITIATIVE.md §3.2 but the document also names "ground in what gsd-2 actually exposes (slice 4)" — the v1-GSD vocabulary is present but constrained by source-grounding requirement.
   388	
   389	**Class B — substantive but non-disposition-changing.**
   390	- Vocabulary or weighting shapes the analysis but the downstream conclusions remain valid under corrected framing.
   391	- Could be revised by re-articulating the affected paragraphs without changing §2.1 / §5 dispositions.
   392	- Example shape: an R-strategy section discusses R2 in thin-layer terms but the conclusion (R2 viable but with caveats) holds under runtime-application framing too.
   393	
   394	**Class C — load-bearing for §2.1 / §5 dispositions.**
   395	- Vocabulary or weighting shapes a conclusion that would change if the framing were corrected.
   396	- Revision before §2.1 / §5 adjudication is warranted.
   397	- Example shape: §5.2 R-mix integration treats R4 as elevated-from-cancellation primarily for release/RC/staging when under runtime-application framing R4 should be primary for headless/RPC/MCP surfaces independent of release-coordination — different incubation R-mix shape.
   398	
   399	**Calibration discipline.** When uncertain between classes, the auditor names the uncertainty and lists what would resolve it. Do not over-classify Class C (false positives erode trust); do not under-classify (false negatives miss the audit's point). The auditor's confidence on each classification is recorded per-finding.
   400	
   401	## §8. Disposition pathway (post-audit)
   402	
   403	After auditor produces `FINDINGS.md`, the disposition pathway is:
   404	
   405	1. **Logan reviews findings.** Reads the summary + Class C items + sample of Class A/B for calibration. If Step-2 fired, reads the differential analysis especially.
   406	2. **Logan disposes** one of:
   407	   - **(a) Commit-as-is.** Premise-bleed is absent or Class A only; SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md commits without revision.
   408	   - **(b) Commit-with-addendum.** Class B/C items are tractable as a §7 addendum to SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md; Claude drafts addendum; commit follows.
   409	   - **(c) Revise-before-commit.** Class C items affect §2.1 / §5 disposition shape; Claude revises affected sections; re-run alignment check; commit follows.
   410	3. **Disposition recorded** at `DISPOSITION.md` in this audit folder. Records: what Logan disposed; reasoning; addendum shape (if (b)); revisions made (if (c)); cross-reference to comparison-drafting decisions log + DECISION-SPACE.md §1.17.
   411	
   412	The auditor produces a non-binding disposition signal (per §6.1 §5 + §6.2 §10) that helps Logan see the per-option reasoning; Logan binds.
   413	
   414	## §9. Conditional structure
   415	
   416	**What would change this spec.**
   417	
   418	- **If Logan reads the lens as wrongly-shaped** (e.g., the v1-GSD vs runtime-application binary is too coarse; the actual concern is finer-grained): revise §2 lens definition.
   419	- **If Logan reads the auditor selection as wrong** (e.g., pre-commit two-step always; or cross-vendor-only single-step; or same-vendor with shared-frame caveat): revise §3 per the alternatives in DECISION-SPACE.md §1.17 "What would change the decision."
   420	- **If Logan reads the artifact list as too narrow or too broad**: revise §4.1 per scope adjustment.
   421	- **If Logan reads the grounding hybrid as risky** (e.g., source-reading creates substance-territory door): drop to prior-audit-only; revise §4.2.
   422	- **If Logan reads the negative-space check as over-engineered**: relax §5.2.3 to optional; revise §2.4 coupling.
   423	- **If Logan reads the vetted-replacement vocabulary as over-engineered**: drop §2.3 lookup; revise §2.2 to "be more careful" without explicit replacements.
   424	- **If Logan reads the classification rubric as too coarse**: refine §7.
   425	
   426	**What this spec does not foreclose.**
   427	
   428	- Whether to expand to substance-audit if premise-bleed audit surfaces source-claim issues (it shouldn't, per scope, but if it does — those go to a substance follow-up, not this audit).
   429	- Whether the SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md draft itself needs structural revision beyond §7 addendum (only if Class C items are pervasive enough that addendum-shape doesn't suffice).
   430	- Whether to add a third audit step (e.g., independent third-synthesizer comparison) if Step-2 differential surfaces unresolvable register/substance conflicts.
   431	
   432	## §10. Cost estimate (per F7 disposition)
   433	
   434	### §10.1 Read budget per artifact
   435	
   436	- **Full read.** INITIATIVE.md; SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md §0/§2/§5/§6; SYNTHESIS-CROSS.md §0/§5/§6.
   437	- **Targeted read.** DECISION-SPACE.md (§1.2/§1.7/§1.8/§3); SYNTHESIS.md (§0/§1/§2.1/§2.5); framing-widening (§1/§2/§3/§4/§9).
   438	- **Scan only.** orchestration preamble; slice prompts (`slice-01-*.md` through `slice-05-*.md`); synthesis-spec; audit-spec — unless propagation-sampling fires per §5.2.5.
   439	- **Conditional sampling.** Slice outputs: only if a Class B/C candidate triggers per §5.2.5; max 3-5 sections; ~10-15 min per section sampled.
   440	- **Conditional grounding.** Source-reading fallback per §4.2: only when prior-audit grounding doesn't cover a specific claim; max 5 file reads; ~5-10 min per file.
   441	
   442	### §10.2 Time budget
   443	
   444	- **Step-1 cross-vendor baseline:** ~1-1.5 hr wall-clock for codex GPT-5.5 high pass over the artifact set under the §10.1 read budget.
   445	  - Plus ~10-15 min × N (max 3-5) if propagation-sampling fires.
   446	  - Plus ~5-10 min × M (max 5) if source-reading fallback fires.
   447	- **Step-2 same-vendor stress (conditional):** ~30-60 min Claude-xhigh pass + ~30 min differential analysis. Fires only if Step-1 returns Class C.
   448	- **Logan disposition review:** ~15-30 min (more if Step-2 fired).
   449	- **Post-disposition Claude work:** 0 lines (commit-as-is) / 50-150 lines addendum / 100-400 lines revisions.
   450	
   451	### §10.3 Total time-to-§2.1+§5-adjudication
   452	
   453	- **Lower bound** (Class A only; no escalation; no addendum): ~1.5-2 hr.
   454	- **Mid-range** (Class B or B/C minor; escalation fires; addendum): ~2.5-3.5 hr.
