   487	### §1.17 v1-GSD premise-bleed audit methodology — two-step conditional vendor + required negative-space + hybrid grounding + vetted-replacement vocabulary
   488	
   489	**Decision.** Following the cross-vendor (GPT-5.5 xhigh) review of the original AUDIT-SPEC.md draft (review: `.planning/gsd-2-uplift/audits/2026-04-28-v1-gsd-mental-model-premise-bleed-audit/AUDIT-SPEC-REVIEW.md`; deliberation: `.planning/deliberations/2026-04-28-audit-spec-review-deliberation.md`), the v1-GSD mental-model premise-bleed audit's methodology is established at this shape:
   490	
   491	1. **Vendor selection — two-step conditional.** Step-1 cross-vendor codex GPT-5.5 high baseline pass under minimal lens-spec; Step-2 same-vendor adversarial-auditor-xhigh stress + differential analysis fires *only if* Step-1 returns Class C candidates. Pre-commit to floor + escalate on evidence (mirrors B2 selective-audit discipline at §1.12).
   492	2. **Lens — vocabulary scan + required negative-space check.** Auditor searches for v1-GSD vocabulary AND asks the negative-space questions (which runtime-application surfaces are absent or late despite being source-central; does question-order make skills/workflow-markdown easy to see and runtime-application surfaces harder to see; does the artifact treat R4 as add-on despite headless/RPC/MCP being first-class GSD-2 surfaces). Negative-space check is *required*, not optional.
   493	3. **Lens vocabulary — vetted-replacement language with citations.** AUDIT-SPEC.md §2 carries explicit replacement vocabulary (per finding 4 corrections: `gsd headless` not `--mode headless`; "GSD CLI/application layer built around vendored, modified Pi-derived packages" not "vendored modified Pi fork"; "core GSD uses extension machinery" with source citation, not all-purpose "core GSD is itself a Pi extension" shortcut). Citations to META-SYNTHESIS or specific source files per item; auditor inherits vetted vocabulary, not "be more careful."
   494	4. **Scope — slice-output targeted sampling allowed under hard cap.** Slice outputs move from out-of-scope to targeted-sampling-allowed: if a Class B/C candidate appears in a primary or secondary artifact, auditor inspects corresponding slice-output section to determine whether premise actually propagated; cite verbatim; do not re-audit whole slices. Hard cap: max 3-5 slice-output sections sampled per audit run total.
   495	5. **Grounding — hybrid (prior-audit primary + narrow source-reading fallback under soft-cap-with-overflow).** Auditor reads prior cross-vendor-codebase-understanding-audit's META-SYNTHESIS.md + GATE-2-DISPOSITION.md + relevant Wave 2 sections as primary grounding for "what GSD-2 actually is." META-SYNTHESIS coverage of runtime-application surfaces is substantial (§1 plural-surface explicit naming; §2 item 1 corrected Pi-fork phrasing; §2 item 2 typed runtime-surface labels; §2 item 3 seven-category typed extension vocabulary; §3 seven prohibited articulations; §5 R4 elevation) — fallback should fire rarely. Narrow source-reading allowed as fallback: **soft default ~5 gsd-2 source file reads per audit run** (not hard cap); overflow allowed when auditor flags + justifies in FINDINGS §4 self-flagged-concerns (count exceeded; per-read fact-grounding-vs-architectural-inference justification; findings grounded); Logan disposes overflow (accept / reclassify under-grounded findings / reject + discount). Use only for fact-grounding (verifying command name, file path, schema field); not for architectural inference; citation required (file:line). Soft-cap-with-overflow is evidence-adaptive (analogous to vendor-selection rule 1 conditional escalation): default low + explicit overflow protocol when justified. The cap applies *only* to gsd-2 source-code reads under the fallback clause, not to reading audited artifacts or prior-audit grounding inputs.
   496	6. **Output — non-binding disposition signal (rename) + per-option justification.** AUDIT-SPEC.md §6 output-template renames "Recommendation shape" to "Non-binding disposition signal" with required per-option justification: auditor states *why* Logan might choose each plausible disposition (commit-as-is / commit-with-addendum / revise-before-commit) given the findings; auditor does not pick one. Actual disposition lives in DISPOSITION.md.
   497	7. **Cost — full/targeted/scan-only read budget + conditional add-ons.** AUDIT-SPEC.md §10 specifies per-artifact read-mode (full / targeted / scan-only) + conditional add-ons (~10-15 min per slice-output sampled per scope rule 4; ~30-60 min Step-2 stress + ~30 min differential per vendor rule 1). Total revised audit-time: 1-3 hours depending on escalation.
   498	
   499	**Operationally.**
   500	
   501	- AUDIT-SPEC.md is revised in-place per the §6 revision-action table in the deliberation log; sections affected: §2 (lens) + §3 (vendor) + §4 (scope) + §5 (method) + §6 (output) + §10 (cost). Estimated ~30-50% rewrite.
   502	- Auditor dispatch follows the revised spec; Step-1 cross-vendor codex first; Step-2 conditional on Class C return.
   503	- DISPOSITION.md in audit folder records actual audit's findings disposition (commit-as-is / commit-with-addendum / revise-before-commit on SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md) post-FINDINGS.md.
   504	- §2.1 + §5 incubation adjudication on SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md proceeds after audit lands and disposition is recorded.
   505	
   506	**Full reasoning.**
   507	
   508	The original Claude-drafted AUDIT-SPEC.md (created 2026-04-28 ~11:42) recommended same-vendor adversarial-auditor-xhigh as baseline auditor on the strength of M1 register-catch property (METHODOLOGY.md:104-115). Logan commissioned an independent cross-vendor review (GPT-5.5 xhigh; output at AUDIT-SPEC-REVIEW.md ~17:16; disposition: revise-before-dispatch). The review surfaced 7 findings (4 Material / 2 Moderate / 1 Minor) which were adjudicated in the deliberation log §5 (Claude-disposed per Logan's 2026-04-28 authorization to perform adjudication and write disposition).
   509	
   510	The most load-bearing finding (F1) was that same-vendor baseline cannot self-detect a Claude+Logan shared-frame failure — which is exactly the v1-GSD-bleed concern. The shared-frame diagnosis cites SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md §4.1's M1 inversion observation: M1's register-vs-substance asymmetry is empirically more complex than the original claim; cross-vendor surfaced the framing-leakage caveat same-vendor missed. Building a premise-bleed audit on a property the comparison itself documented as failing in this vendor pair is structurally incoherent.
   511	
   512	The two-step conditional vendor disposition (rule 1) sits between the reviewer's two-step (always run both same-vendor + cross-vendor) and Claude's earlier three-step extension (always run cross-vendor + same-vendor + differential). Cross-vendor baseline is the structural floor — the cross-vendor reader is the one who can detect shared Claude+Logan framing. Same-vendor stress adds value only when cross-vendor surfaces Class C candidates Claude reading might re-classify or supplement. Below Class C, same-vendor stress likely catches register-shaped items below load-bearing-ness threshold and is not worth the dispatch. Conditional escalation matches B2's existing per-slice-W2-audit-disposition discipline.
   513	
   514	The negative-space check (rule 2) is the review's most important methodological catch (per deliberation log §4.1). Vocabulary-only lens catches what was *said*, not what was *omitted*. Premise-bleed via omission is exactly the failure mode Logan's premise-correction concern flagged. The original spec's lens-questions named the right targets (under-weighting; question-shape) but the method didn't operationalize how to find them. The negative-space check fixes this directly and couples to grounding (rule 5) for the reference frame.
   515	
   516	The vetted-replacement vocabulary (rule 3) goes beyond the reviewer's "be more careful" recommendation because for an audit specifically about vocabulary precision, "be more careful" without explicit replacements reintroduces the original problem (the auditor constructs its own replacements; inherits compression-shape). Vetted-replacement-with-citations transfers the precision-burden from auditor judgment to spec authorship.
   517	
   518	The scope hybrid (rules 4 + 5) resolves the original spec's internal contradiction: motivation invoked propagation but scope excluded slice outputs, and grounding was forbidden but corrected-frame claims rest on source-grounded knowledge. Targeted-sampling under hard cap + prior-audit-first grounding with narrow-source-reading fallback are bounded inclusions that fix the contradiction without expanding into substance-audit territory.
   519	
   520	The output rename (rule 6) and read budget (rule 7) are localized cleanups: the original "Recommendation shape" conflated auditor-signal with Logan-disposition; the original cost estimate was sloppy. Rename + per-option justification preserves auditor's helpful signal while honoring Logan-disposes-only discipline; explicit read budget with conditional add-ons makes the scope-expansion paths honest.
   521	
   522	**Determining assumptions.**
   523	
   524	1. v1-GSD-bleed concern is plausibly load-bearing for §2.1 (R4 disposition-timing — exactly where runtime-application weighting matters) and §5.2 (R-mix decomposition shape — depends on which surfaces are first-class), per SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md §4.4 + Logan's premise-correction message.
   525	2. M1 register-vs-substance asymmetry is empirically more complex than original claim (per SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md §4.1); cross-vendor catches what same-vendor cannot detect when same-vendor shares the artifact's framing. Vendor selection rule rests on this.
   526	3. Prior cross-vendor-codebase-understanding-audit is substantially robust against v1-GSD-bleed (because it was cross-vendor) but not necessarily fully robust at the runtime-application-surface-weighting level. Hybrid grounding (prior-audit primary + narrow source-reading fallback) hedges against this residual risk.
   527	4. Cost of mis-calibrated §2.1 / §5 incubation disposition under bled-frame is materially higher than cost of running the audit. 1-3 hour audit-time + ~45-90 min spec-revision-time is justified.
   528	5. Auditor calibration on bounded sampling (rule 4 hard cap; rule 5 max 5 source reads) holds in practice. Without this assumption, scope creep into substance-audit territory becomes a real risk.
   529	
   530	**What would change the decision.**
   531	
   532	- *If Logan reads bleed concern as cosmetic Class-A-only*: simplify rule 1 to cross-vendor-only single-step (no conditional escalation); drop rule 2 negative-space check to optional; drop rule 5 source-reading fallback; spec revision becomes lighter (~15-25% rewrite).
   533	- *If Logan reads bleed as definitively load-bearing*: force three-step (Claude's earlier extension; same-vendor stress always runs) per rule 1; no other changes.
   534	- *If Logan distrusts conditional dispositions in general* (per §1.12 "If you'd rather not maintain per-slice audit-disposition decisions"): pre-commit to two-step always per reviewer's recommendation; drop conditional escalation.
   535	- *If Logan distrusts the "small substance-territory door" of source-reading fallback* (rule 5): drop source-reading; prior-audit grounding only.
   536	- *If Logan reads vetted-replacement extension as over-engineering* (rule 3): drop the extension; "be more careful" instruction in spec; risk additional auditor inheritance.
   537	- *If Logan reads cross-vendor codex baseline as too independent* (i.e., codex doesn't natively know v1-GSD; lens-construction in spec is necessary): swap rule 1's Step-1 to same-vendor adversarial-auditor with explicit shared-frame caveat acknowledged in spec; less-clean structurally but better lens-comprehension.
   538	- *If prior-audit's META-SYNTHESIS is found unreliable* on inspection (rule 5 grounding): swap rule 5 to source-reading-primary instead of fallback; heavier audit-time but cleaner independence.
   539	
   540	**Confidence.** Medium-high. Each rule rests on specific evidence (SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md §4.1 inversion observation; reviewer's findings; deliberation log §3 analysis). Rules 1 + 2 + 5 form a coherent triad addressing "what stable independent reference frame can the auditor anchor to" (per deliberation log §4.2). Rules 4 + 6 + 7 are localized refinements. Rule 3 (vetted-replacement) is the rule most likely to be revised post-spec-revision if Logan reads the extension as over-engineering. Adjudication-uncertainty notes per finding live in deliberation log §6.
   541	
   542	**Log reference.** `.planning/deliberations/2026-04-28-audit-spec-review-deliberation.md` (full deliberation; §3 Claude analysis; §4 cross-cutting observations; §5 per-finding adjudications with rationale + where-Logan-might-differ + revision-implication; §6 revision-action table). Predecessor methodological observation: `.planning/gsd-2-uplift/exploration/SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md` §4.1 (M1 mixed observation) + §4.4 (framing-import drift signal that motivated the audit). Predecessor decisions: §1.12 (B2 selective-audit discipline that conditional-escalation mirrors); §1.13 (B3 vendor-scope that this rule extends).
   543	
   544	**Realized outcome (post-execution, 2026-04-29).** The audit-arc was executed end-to-end and the methodology held under execution. Step-1 cross-vendor codex GPT-5.5 high returned 6 instances (1A/5B/0C; no auto-Step-2 trigger per rule 1's conditional-escalation default). Logan invoked rule 1's manual-escalation discretion (`AUDIT-SPEC.md §3.4`) to obtain Step-2 as an **independent same-vendor read** rather than as the spec-default differential read — a deviation from the rule's default-shape that traded third-reader-independence-of-differential for cleaner vendor-position-symmetric evidence. Step-2 same-vendor Claude xhigh returned 9 instances (4A/3B/2C narrowly load-bearing; isolation clean). Main-thread DIFFERENTIAL.md reconciled the two reads as vendor-position-symmetric complementary findings: cross-vendor caught vocabulary-import bleed; same-vendor caught integration-grammar-as-fact at meta-level. Logan disposed commit-with-addendum (option (b) per `AUDIT-SPEC.md §8`); SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md §7 audit addendum landed; DISPOSITION.md recorded. The audit folder carries the full trail: AUDIT-SPEC.md + AUDIT-SPEC-REVIEW.md + FINDINGS.md + FINDINGS-STEP2.md + DIFFERENTIAL.md + DISPOSITION.md.
   545	
