   510	The most load-bearing finding (F1) was that same-vendor baseline cannot self-detect a Claude+Logan shared-frame failure — which is exactly the v1-GSD-bleed concern. The shared-frame diagnosis cites SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md §4.1's M1 inversion observation: M1's register-vs-substance asymmetry is empirically more complex than the original claim; cross-vendor surfaced the framing-leakage caveat same-vendor missed. Building a premise-bleed audit on a property the comparison itself documented as failing in this vendor pair is structurally incoherent.
