   544	**Realized outcome (post-execution, 2026-04-29).** The audit-arc was executed end-to-end and the methodology held under execution. Step-1 cross-vendor codex GPT-5.5 high returned 6 instances (1A/5B/0C; no auto-Step-2 trigger per rule 1's conditional-escalation default). Logan invoked rule 1's manual-escalation discretion (`AUDIT-SPEC.md §3.4`) to obtain Step-2 as an **independent same-vendor read** rather than as the spec-default differential read — a deviation from the rule's default-shape that traded third-reader-independence-of-differential for cleaner vendor-position-symmetric evidence. Step-2 same-vendor Claude xhigh returned 9 instances (4A/3B/2C narrowly load-bearing; isolation clean). Main-thread DIFFERENTIAL.md reconciled the two reads as vendor-position-symmetric complementary findings: cross-vendor caught vocabulary-import bleed; same-vendor caught integration-grammar-as-fact at meta-level. Logan disposed commit-with-addendum (option (b) per `AUDIT-SPEC.md §8`); SYNTHESIS-COMPARISON.md §7 audit addendum landed; DISPOSITION.md recorded. The audit folder carries the full trail: AUDIT-SPEC.md + AUDIT-SPEC-REVIEW.md + FINDINGS.md + FINDINGS-STEP2.md + DIFFERENTIAL.md + DISPOSITION.md.
   545	
   546	**Lessons distilled for future audits.**
   547	- The cross-vendor + same-vendor-xhigh pairing produced *complementary* findings rather than *redundant* ones — cross-vendor catches vocabulary-import; same-vendor catches integration-grammar-as-fact. This is the M1 paired-review property in action; the audit's evidence for it is independent of any specific finding. Argues for retaining this discipline shape in future premise-bleed or framing-leak audits.
